headline.main: AUSTRALIANS RAID RABAUL PORT AGAIN; Japanese Invasion Fleet Gets Bombing in the Harbor of New Britain Island 4 NEW GUINEA TOWNS HIT Officials Meet in Melbourne to Make Secret Plans to Meet Increased Threat

lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia, Feb. 1 (U.P.) -- Australian bombers made another smash at the Japanese invasion armada in the harbor of Rabaul, New Britain Island, as Japanese war planes continued raids on towns in northeast New Guinea, it was announced.
abstract: Jap planes bomb Salamaua, Wau and Bulolo
